            <h2 class="text-center">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            
            <div class="row row-centered">
                <div class="col-centered faq" style=" text-align:center;">
                    <strong><a href='/faq_business.jsp' style='color: white;'>Click here if you are an employer</a></strong>
                 <dl>

                    <dt>Q) What is Clockwork?</dt>
                    <dd>Clockwork is a free online marketplace to match ad-hoc job-seekers with businesses. You can apply for job posts to indicate your interests to be hired for the businesses. </dd>

                    <dt>Q) Why should I use Clockwork?</dt>
                    <dd>It is not only a platform for you to find ad-hoc jobs fast. This unique platform we created for you also allows for quick and fuss free application of a job, no more CVs, no more resumes, and if possible, no more interviews!   </dd>

                    <dt>Q) Is it free to sign up?</dt>
                    <dd>Yes! It is completely free to sign up and use the services on Clockwork. We do not charge a commission or any fee. There are no hidden charges or fees! Imagine if your friend introduced you to another friend and later on asking you for a small fee, how ridiculous would that be? Same here at Clockwork. we created this platform to connect 2 sides that needs each other, hence we want to remain this connection without having to charge you any 'connecting fees'

                        If you are a business looking to list your opportunities with us, it is as easy as signing up with us on Clockworksg.com! We would love to meet you to go through how our system works.</dd>

                        <dt>Q) Are businesses real?</dt>
                        <dd>We at Clockwork believe in tangible things, just like jobs and money, hence we actively seek out to talk to businesses directly to find you the best opportunities in the market. Visiting the business, talking to the managers, getting rejected, getting questioned and all ways to help you increase your choices. </dd>

                        <dt>Q) What do you mean by Applying for a job?</dt>
                        <dd>For Job Seekers, after browsing or searching our job listings either through our web or mobile (Android, iOS) platforms , it is time to take action when you have found something that interests you. By applying for a job post that you are able to work for, businesses are notified of your interest and they are able to assess if this is a good match for them. If all things are good, businesses will offer you the job and upon your confirmation, hooray, you have just got yourself a job at that stipulated date and timing.</dd>

                        <dt>Q) Why should I provide my mobile number?</dt>
                        <dd>This is to notify job-seekers of useful updates from businesses immediately.</dd>

                        <dt>Q) Will I get spammed?</dt>
                        <dd>We fully support the Personal Data Protection Commission and aim to comply fully with its requirements, including respecting the "Do Not Call" registry settings. </dd>

                        <dt>Q) Why should I provide my profile picture?</dt>
                        <dd>Adding a picture to your profile is a great way to reach out and increase your visibility to businesses. Bring on your brightest smile and make an impact!</dd>

                        <dt>Q) So how do I find out more about the opportunity?</dt>
                        <dd>Click, click, click! There are several ways to find out more about an opportunity: from our main page, simply click on an interesting listing. This would bring up the listings page with the relevant details, including what the businesses are looking for and clicking on the slots shown would bring up individual slots details including when, how long, where and the hourly rate.</dd> 

                        <dt>Q) What if I don't know what to look for but I have free time this weekend or from the current day itself?</dt>
                        <dd>Just sort our job listing based on the start date of a job, and you will be able to find jobs that are happening closest to your current date. Hence you can find out what ad-hoc job you would like to work based on their start date and time, and also, more importantly you can sort them based on salary! After all, who is not seeking to earn some money doing these jobs.</dd>


                        <dt>Q) What is the system requirements for using Clockwork?</dt>
                        <dd>You need an Internet connection, along with either Chrome/Safari/Firefox and above. Chrome is highly recommended as it currently provides the best user experience.</dd>

                        <dt>Q) How do I know if your application has been accepted?</dt>
                        <dd>An email will be sent to you, and if you have our ClockworkSG Mobile App (Android, iOS), you will also receive a notification on it. You can also click on the notification icon to view your latest notifications or just check your Dashboard to see which of your applications have been confirmed and you are offered by an employer. </dd>

                        <dt>Q) Are you having problems with applying for jobs?</dt>
                        <dd>We've made sure that the system is as easy to use as possible, so if you are not able to apply for a job or somehow are having some issues with the application, please drop us a mail and we will definitely solve it for you!</dd>

                        <dt>Q) How long does it take for business to respond?</dt>
                        <dd>As soon as you have applied, business is updated with a notification email of your application. They can view this information in their email and also on their Dashboard as well. After that, it is up to the business on how quickly they can reply.</dd>

                        <dt>Q) Where and how do I collect my money?</dt>
                        <dd>We serve as matchmakers of ad-hoc jobs to part timers and businesses, we do not pay anyone who uses our site and services. Payment is directly paid to you from business at their usual scheduled payroll date or any payment agreements made between you and the business.</dd>

                    </dl>
